Redmond) ‘le Gros’ <i>FitzGerald</i> (died after 1185) led the invasion of Ireland on behalf of Strongbow in 1170. A branch of the family held the title Knight of Glin from at least 1299–2011."],"variants":[{"name":"Jarrell","meanings":["Irish: altered form of   Fitzgerald  .","English (Kent and Middlesex; of Norman origin): variant of <b>Jarrold</b>, itself a variant of   Gerald  ."]},{"name":"Fitz","meanings":["English: from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (from Latin <i>filius</i>), used originally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same personal name and then conventionalized as a hereditary surname, or short for a surname of which <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ was the first element, for example   Fitzhenry   and   Fitzroy  .","Altered form of English   Fitch  .","German: from a vernacular pet form of the personal name <i>Vinzenz</i> (see   Vincent  ) or <i>Vitus</i> (see   Vito  , compare   Veit  ). Compare also   Fietz  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Fitzmaurice","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Aidan, Ciaran, Colm.","Irish: from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (see   Fitz  ) + the personal name <i>Maurice</i> (see   Morris   1), ‘son of <i>Maurice</i>’. This surname is common in Ireland, where it has also been Gaelicized as <b>Mac Muiris</b>. The Irish family of <i>Fitzmaurice</i> share a common Norman ancestry with the   Fitzgerald   family. They can be traced to Thomas <i>Fitzmaurice</i>, whose brother Gerald was the ancestor of the Irish Fitzgerald dynasty. Their father was Maurice Fitzgerald, a Norman baron (died 1176)."],"variants":[{"name":"Fitz","meanings":["Either a short form of any of the numerous names representing a transferred use of a surname formed with the Anglo-Norman French prefix <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son of ’, as for example   Fitzgerald  ,   Fitzroy  , or a transferred use of the surname <i>Fitz</i>, which may be of the same derivation, but applied originally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same given name, or a local name from Fitz in Shropshire, named with the Old English personal name <i>Fitt</i> + <i>hōh</i> ‘hill spur’."]},{"name":"Fitzmorris","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Fitzmaurice  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"John Fitzmaurice Fitzgerald 6th Earl of Kildare was born in 1385, in Castletown, County Kildare, Ireland as the son of Gerald FitzMaurice FitzGerald 5th Earl of Kildare. He had at least 1 son with Margaret de la Herne. He died on 17 October 1427, in County Kildare, Ireland, at the age of 42, and was buried in Diocese of Dublin, Ireland."},"et":{"1385–17 October 1427":"1385–17. oktoober 1427","1385–1427":"1385–1427","1395–1432":"1395–1432","1398–1452":"1398–1452","1386–1439":"1386–1439","1421–1477":"1421–1477","1363–1428":"1363–1428","1385":"1385","1363":"1363","1395":"1395","17 October 1427":"17. oktoober 1427","1477":"1477","1410":"1410","1421":"1421","1432":"1432","1398":"1398","1386":"1386","1452":"1452","1428":"1428","1439":"1439","1427":"1427","Maynooth, Kildare, Ireland":"Maynooth, County Kildare, Iirimaa","Castletown, County Kildare, Ireland":"Castletown, County Kildare, Iirimaa","All Hallows, Trinity College, Dublin, Ireland":"Diocese of Dublin, Iirimaa","County Kildare, Ireland":"County Kildare, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1385–17 October 1427":"1385–17. lokakuuta 1427","1385–1427":"1385–1427","1395–1432":"1395–1432","1398–1452":"1398–1452","1386–1439":"1386–1439","1421–1477":"1421–1477","1363–1428":"1363–1428","1385":"1385","1363":"1363","1395":"1395","17 October 1427":"17. lokakuuta 1427","1477":"1477","1410":"1410","1421":"1421","1432":"1432","1398":"1398","1386":"1386","1452":"1452","1428":"1428","1439":"1439","1427":"1427","Maynooth, Kildare, Ireland":"Maynooth, 